Elements with the disabled attribute arent interactive, meaning users cannot focus, hover, or click them to trigger a tooltip (or popover). As a workaround, youll want to trigger the tooltip from a wrapper <div> or <span>, ideally made keyboard-focusable using tabIndex="0", and override the pointer-events on the disabled element.
